  "prompt": "Why does the Justin Bieber video Baby have more dislikes than likes?",
  "response": "Justin Bieber's music video \"Baby\" has garnered a significant number of dislikes compared to likes for a variety of reasons. Here are some key points that might explain this phenomenon:\n\n1. **Popularity and Exposure**: As one of the most popular songs during its release, \"Baby\" attracted a vast amount of attention. The wide exposure meant it reached not just fans, but also those who were indifferent or even opposed to his music or public persona.\n\n2. **YouTube's Dislike Button**: \"Baby\" became one of the early examples where the YouTube dislike button was used en masse, almost as a trend. Many people hit the dislike button as a form of expressing their distaste collectively, rather than genuine dislike for the content itself.\n\n3. **Negative Backlash and Internet Culture**: Justin Bieber faced significant backlash and was the subject of many internet jokes and memes around the time the video was released. The dislikes could be part of a broader trend of internet culture where individuals partook in disliking the video as part of an online joke or trend.\n\n4. **Changing Musical Tastes**: Musical preferences change over time, and some people might dislike the video because the style of music or Bieber\u2019s earlier sound might no longer appeal to them.\n\n5. **Competition and Fan Wars**: Often in the music industry, artists and their fan bases are competitive. Rival fans might dislike a video in order to boost another artist they prefer more.\n\n6. **Public Perception**: Justin Bieber's public behavior and controversies have sometimes negatively impacted his reputation, leading to more people being predisposed to dislike his work regardless of the actual content quality.\n\nDespite the dislikes, the video has a high view count and an impressive number of likes as well, highlighting its widespread impact and Bieber's significant fan base.",
